 many years. Following his music studies and time on the music staff at Glyndebourne, Bedford joined the English Opera Group, gradually becoming Britten's trusted surrogate conductor. As Britten's health began to fail, he took on responsibility for the premiere performances of Britten's final opera, Death in Venice, including its US premiere at the Metropolitan Opera, New York, and the dramatic cantata Phaedra among others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aComposerszGreat Britain. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Individual Composer & Musician.2bisacsh  aBenjamin Britten.  aSteuart Bedford.  aclassical music.  amusic career.  amusic conductor.  amusic history.  amusic industry.  amusic performances.  amusic world.  amusical collaborations.  amusical insights.  aopera.1 aGillett, Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311143100040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800107991?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800107991423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800107991/original  a978-3-11-143100-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles